#: templates/wagtail_2fa/device_form.html:13
msgid ""
"\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                Two-Factor authentication is a method for making your "
"account\n"
"                more secure, by requiring you to provide an additional "
"piece\n"
"                of evidence (a factor) next to your password.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                The most common way of providing this secondary factor, is "
"by\n"
"                having one of your devices generate a random code that\n"
"                changes every minute. This is called a One Time Password.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                For generating codes, you can use one of the following "
"apps.\n"
"                You might even have them installed already.\n"
"                <ul>\n"
"                    <li>Google Authenticator for iOS or Android</li>\n"
"                    <li>Microsoft Authenticator</li>\n"
"                    <li>Authy for iOS or Android</li>\n"
"                    <li>\n"
"                        A password manager like 1Password, that also "
"supports\n"
"                        generating One-Time-Passwords\n"
"                    </li>\n"
"                </ul>\n"
"            </p>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                To configure two-factor authentication for your Wagtail CMS\n"
"                account, install one of those apps and scan the below QR\n"
"                code. Note that if you lose or reset your phone, you\n"
"                will no longer be able to log in.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"            "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                L'authentification à deux facteurs est une méthode pour "
"renforcer\n"
"                la sécurité de votre compte, en vous demandant de fournir "
"une\n"
"                preuve supplémentaire (un facteur) en plus de votre mot de "
"passe.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                La façon la plus courante de fournir ce facteur secondaire "
"est\n"
"                d'avoir un de vos appareils qui génère un code aléatoire "
"qui\n"
"                change toutes les minutes. Ceci est appelé un mot de passe à "
"usage unique.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                Pour générer des codes, vous pouvez utiliser l'une des "
"applications suivantes.\n"
"                Vous pourriez même les avoir déjà installées.\n"
"                <ul>\n"
"                    <li>Google Authenticator pour iOS ou Android</li>\n"
"                    <li>Microsoft Authenticator</li>\n"
"                    <li>Authy pour iOS ou Android</li>\n"
"                    <li>\n"
"                        Un gestionnaire de mots de passe comme 1Password, "
"qui prend également\n"
"                        en charge la génération de mots de passe à usage "
"unique\n"
"                    </li>\n"
"                </ul>\n"
"            </p>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                Pour configurer l'authentification à deux facteurs pour "
"votre compte\n"
"                Wagtail CMS, installez l'une de ces applications et scannez "
"le code QR\n"
"                ci-dessous. Notez que si vous perdez ou réinitialisez votre "
"téléphone,\n"
"                vous ne pourrez plus vous connecter.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"            "

